def lottery(s):
    return "".join(dict.fromkeys(filter(str.isdigit, s))) or "One more run!"

def lottery(stg):
    return "".join(c for c in sorted(set(stg), key=stg.index) if c.isdecimal()) or "One more run!"

def lottery(s):
    return ''.join({i:1 for i in s if i.isdigit()}) or 'One more run!'

def lottery(s):
    result = set()
    result_seen = result.add
    result = [char for char in s if char.isdigit() and not (char in result or result_seen(char))]
    return "".join(result) if "".join(result).isnumeric() else "One more run!"
